# Trivy Ignore File
# Suppresses misconfig findings that are intentional for a reusable module library.
# Posture enforcement is the caller's responsibility, not the module's.
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# AVD-AWS-0123: MFA not enforced for IAM groups
# IAM group modules expose this as a configurable policy; the caller attaches MFA policies
AVD-AWS-0123

# AVD-AWS-0001: API Gateway access logging not configured
# Exposed as access_log_settings variable; caller provides the log destination ARN
AVD-AWS-0001

# AVD-AWS-0003: API Gateway stage-level logging not configured
# Exposed as default_route_settings/logging variables; caller controls log level
AVD-AWS-0003

# AVD-AWS-0010: CloudFront distribution logging not enabled
# Exposed as logging_config variable; caller provides the S3 log bucket
AVD-AWS-0010

# AVD-AWS-0012: CloudFront distribution allows unencrypted (HTTP) communications
# Exposed as viewer_protocol_policy variable; caller enforces HTTPS-only if required
AVD-AWS-0012

# AVD-AWS-0027: SQS queue not encrypted with CMK
# Exposed as kms_master_key_id variable; caller provides the KMS key
AVD-AWS-0027

# AVD-AWS-0053: Load balancer is exposed publicly
# By design for internet-facing load balancers; caller sets internal variable
AVD-AWS-0053

# AVD-AWS-0062: IAM password policy allows max age greater than 90 days
# Exposed as max_password_age variable; caller sets the policy
AVD-AWS-0062

# AVD-AWS-0066: SQS queue policy is too permissive
# Exposed as policy variable; caller provides the least-privilege policy document
AVD-AWS-0066

# AVD-AWS-0089: S3 bucket has public access block disabled
# Exposed as block_public_acls/block_public_policy variables; caller enforces access control
AVD-AWS-0089

# AVD-AWS-0090: S3 bucket does not have versioning enabled
# Exposed as versioning variable; caller enables versioning where required
AVD-AWS-0090

# AVD-AWS-0095: SNS topic does not have encryption enabled
# Exposed as kms_master_key_id variable; caller provides the KMS key
AVD-AWS-0095

# AVD-AWS-0132: S3 bucket does not encrypt data with a customer managed key
# Exposed as kms_master_key_id/sse_algorithm variables; caller provides CMK when required
AVD-AWS-0132

# AVD-AWS-0343: RDS/DocumentDB cluster does not have deletion protection enabled
# Exposed as deletion_protection variable; caller enables for production workloads
AVD-AWS-0343
